     1→NOTE: This operation verifies whether newer VM images are available upstream by comparing SHA digests. It uses a temporary
     2→{at_stash_machine}
     3→with crane installed to query registries without modifying configuration.
     4→
     5→// ⟦axs_behavior⟧
     6→. *Create Temporary {at_stash_machine}*:
     7→.. {rbbc_use}
     8→{rbrr_stash_machine} as machine name
     9→.. {rbbc_call}
    10→podman machine init for `{rbrr_stash_machine}`
    11→.. {rbbc_call}
    12→podman machine start for `{rbrr_stash_machine}`
    13→.. {rbbc_call}
    14→installation of crane from {rbrr_crane_tar_gz}
    15→.. {rbbc_require}
    16→crane installation successful
    17→.. {rbbc_store}
    18→`«STASH_MACHINE»` as temporary machine identifier
    19→
    20→. *Query Upstream Image*:
    21→.. {rbbc_use}
    22→{rbrr_chosen_vmimage_origin}:{rbrr_chosen_podman_version} as query target
    23→.. {rbbc_call}
    24→crane digest for upstream image
    25→.. {rbbc_store}
    26→`«UPSTREAM_SHA»` from crane response
    27→.. {rbbc_fatal}
    28→if no valid digest returned: "Failed to query upstream image digest"
    29→
    30→. *Verify Custom FQIN*:
    31→.. {rbbc_require}
    32→{rbrr_chosen_vmimage_fqin} defined
    33→.. If {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_fqin} differs from {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_origin}:{rbrr_chosen_podman_version}:
    34→... {rbbc_call}
    35→crane digest for {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_fqin}
    36→... {rbbc_store}
    37→`«FQIN_SHA»` from crane response
    38→... Compare `«FQIN_SHA»` with `«UPSTREAM_SHA»`
    39→... {rbbc_warn}
    40→if digests differ: "Custom FQIN digest does not match upstream"
    41→
    42→. *Cleanup Resources*:
    43→.. {rbbc_call}
    44→podman machine stop for `«STASH_MACHINE»`
    45→.. {rbbc_call}
    46→podman machine rm for `«STASH_MACHINE»`
    47→.. {rbbc_require}
    48→no orphaned resources remain
    49→
    50→// ⟦axs_outputs⟧
    51→. *Report Findings*:
    52→.. {rbbc_show}
    53→current {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_sha} value (if set)
    54→.. {rbbc_show}
    55→latest upstream SHA: `«UPSTREAM_SHA»`
    56→.. {rbbc_show}
    57→required action:
    58→... If {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_sha} not set: "Please set RBRR_CHOSEN_VMIMAGE_SHA to «UPSTREAM_SHA»"
    59→... If {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_sha} differs from `«UPSTREAM_SHA»`: "Update available"
    60→... If {rbrr_chosen_vmimage_sha} matches `«UPSTREAM_SHA»`: "System is current"
    61→
    62→// ⟦axs_completion⟧
    63→Successful execution reports upstream VM image status and indicates whether updates are available.
    64→

